<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> La Salle Films Fla. 'ER' Episode </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLERMONT, Fla. (AP) -- Central Florida got a little taste of  
Hollywood when ``ER'' rolled into town to shoot an episode 
featuring Eriq La Salle. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's pretty exciting, bringing some of the big productions out  
to our little lakes,'' Scott Hunnel, who watched the filming with 
his wife from their boat, said Monday. ``It's nice to be able to go 
out and see a movie like this ... and be able to point out there's 
our hometown.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In the episode, La Salle's character, Dr. Peter Benton, spends  
his vacation working in a rural area of Mississippi to raise money 
for medical care for his deaf son. 
</P>
<P>
	La Salle said the show highlights a real problem facing rural  
communities around the nation. 
</P>
<P>
	``We have these rural towns that have no health care and we're  
in no rush to fix it,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The episode is scheduled to air Feb. 25.  
</P>
</TEXT>
