<HEADLINE> Injured Rios Out of Aussie Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) -- Marcelo Rios will not get that  
elusive grand slam title at this Australian Open. 
</P>
<P>
	A back injury forced him to withdraw Monday from the year's  
first major championship. 
</P>
<P>
	The Chilean, ranked No. 2, spent six weeks at No. 1 last year  
before Pete Sampras overtook him to finish on top for a sixth 
straight year. Sampras is fatigued and not playing in Australia. 
</P>
<P>
	Rios, who lost in the finals to Petr Korda in Australia last  
year, has been told to rest at least four weeks, and that could 
cost him any chance of reaching No. 1 this year. 
</P>
<P>
	The ATP Tour said Rios could plunge as low as No. 7 after this  
tournament because of his withdrawal. 
</P>
<P>
	Tournament doctor David Bolzonello said Rios should not play  
again until middle or late March. There are two major events in the 
United States that month -- at Indian Wells, Calif., and Key 
Biscayne, Fla. -- and Rios is defending champion in both. 
</P>
<P>
	The ATP system, in which players have to defend points won the  
previous year, works against Rios, whose title defense at last 
week's Auckland Open was also spoiled by the injury. 
</P>
<P>
	Bolzonello said an MRI on Monday showed a small fracture in one  
vertebrae. 
</P>
<P>
	``These injuries are potentially serious for all athletes  
involved in sports that involve extension of the back,'' Bolzonello 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	``In Marcelo's case we feel it's new, we've diagnosed it within  
a few days of it appearing. And now we know it's there, he can 
follow the appropriate treatment, which is essentially rest. And 
there's a very good chance it will heal without any concerns in the 
next few weeks.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bolzonello said Rios should take a few extra weeks to make sure  
his rehabilitation succeeds. 
</P>
<P>
	``This fracture is very minor,'' he said. ``Even though it's his  
vertebrae and it sounds dramatic, it'll heal as well as if he'd 
broken his finger, in three or four weeks.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
