<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Abortion Foe Kopp May Be in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Federal investigators have evidence that the  
abortion foe wanted for questioning in the sniper slaying of a 
Buffalo, N.Y., doctor may have fled to Mexico, a Justice Department 
official said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	There is some evidence that anti-abortion activist James Charles  
Kopp, 44, was driven to Mexico by a female friend after the Oct. 23 
shooting, this official said. And a Customs Service videotape from 
a border crossing point shows the woman's car returning from Mexico 
later, according to the official who requested anonymity. 
</P>
<P>
	Newsweek magazine reported that credit card receipts reflect a  
trip to Mexico by the woman. In its Jan. 25 issue, Newsweek also 
said FBI Director Louis Freeh, in Mexico on an official visit last 
week, asked the Mexican government for help locating Kopp. 
</P>
<P>
	The federal official said investigators have recovered fibers at  
the shooting scene that are being tested to see if they can be 
linked to Kopp. 
</P>
<P>
	Kopp is wanted as a material witness in the killing of Dr.  
Barnett Slepian, a 52-year-old obstetrician-gynecologist who 
performed abortions. He was gunned down in the kitchen of his 
suburban Buffalo home by a rifle shot fired from outside. 
</P>
<P>
	Kopp's 1987 Chevrolet Cavalier was discovered last month at  
Newark, N.J., International Airport, the FBI said. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities have said the car was spotted in Amherst, N.Y., a  
Buffalo suburb, in the weeks before Slepian was killed. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators believe the killing is linked to four earlier  
nonfatal shootings targeting doctors who provided abortion services 
in Canada and upstate New York. 
</P>
<P>
	The car had been in the long-term lot about two weeks, said Greg  
Trevor, a spokesman for the Port Authority of New York and New 
Jersey. 
</P>
<P>
	The car had a New Jersey license plate that didn't belong on it.  
FBI Agent Monica Patton in Newark said she couldn't say whether or 
not the plate had been stolen. 
</P>
<P>
	Kopp is believed to have been working on a construction job in  
the metropolitan New York area two days after the shooting, FBI 
Agent Bernard Tolbert said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
