<HEADLINE> Brit Aerospace, Brit GE Talk Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Britain's General Electric Co. PLC and British  
Aerospace PLC confirmed Monday they are in advanced discussions, 
following a published report that they are near a deal involving 
GEC's Marconi defense unit. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wall Street Journal reported Monday that British Aerospace  
is poised to acquire the Marconi defense unit for around $13.3 
billion. 
</P>
<P>
	A deal could be announced this week, the newspaper report said,  
citing people familiar with the discussions. 
</P>
<P>
	British Aerospace had previously confirmed that it was in  
discussions with several possible merger partners, including GEC. 
That company is not related to U.S.-based General Electric. 

</P>
</TEXT>
