<HEADLINE> Excerpts From Letters on Clinton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Excerpts from letters written by constituents to Republican  
Sens. John Chafee of Rhode Island and Slade Gorton of Washington: 
</P>
<P>
	To Chafee:  
</P>
<P>
	--''I have voted for you during your last two terms of office and  
am proud to have done so. ... If President Clinton is impeached I 
will not vote for ANY Republican candidates for office for the next 
eight years.'' From Rumford. 
</P>
<P>
	--''Senator Chafee, please be not the 'voice of compromise,' nor  
the 'reasonable, bipartisan solution to this ordeal' that Clinton 
has no right to even ask for. Instead be the FIRST voice in the 
Senate to speak loudly and clearly for equal justice under the 
law.'' From a Tiverton independent voter. 
</P>
