<HEADLINE> Rapper Awaits Police Report on Gun </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Rapper ODB awaited results Sunday of paraffin  
tests that could indicate whether he fired a gun during an 
encounter with undercover cops on a Brooklyn street. 
</P>
<P>
	Detectives also were seeking a handgun they say was fired after  
police stopped his sport utility truck for a routine traffic 
violation Friday night. As of Sunday, no gun had been found, 
detectives said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 29-year-old Wu-Tang Clan singer has used the name ODB in the  
past and more recently goes by Big Baby Jesus. His real name is 
Russell Jones. 
</P>
<P>
	He pleaded innocent Saturday to attempted murder in the first  
degree, attempted murder in the second degree and two counts of 
criminal weapons possession. The main charge carries a maximum 
penalty of 25 years to life. 
</P>
<P>
	Bail was set at $150,000 and Jones was ordered to reappear in  
court Jan. 21. 
</P>
