<HEADLINE> Dollar, Gold Rise in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar rose against other major currencies in  
European trading today. Gold rose. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.1595, down from $1.1617 on Friday, and  
the dollar was quoted at 114.23 Japanese yen, up from 113.34. In 
New York, the euro was quoted at $1.1600 and the dollar was quoted 
at 114.35 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in London, compared with late Friday: 1.3819  
Swiss francs, up from 1.3737; 1.5246 Canadian dollars, down from 
1.5280. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6535, down from $1.6550. In  
New York, the pound was quoted at $1.6530 at midday. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 1.6868 German marks, up from 1.6836; 
5.6572 French francs, up from 5.6465; 1.9006 Dutch guilders, up 
from 1.8970; 1669.92 Italian lire, up from 1,666.76. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $287.00 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$286.00 on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $286.90, up from $285.70.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold rose $0.60 in Hong Kong to close at $287.05.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.12 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$5.08 bid per troy ounce from Friday. 
</P>
