<HEADLINE> Man Survives Crash, Killed by Pole </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- A man who survived a head-on crash into  
a tree died when he got out of his car and was hit by a utility 
pole. 
</P>
<P>
	Hernan Herrera, 36, was killed instantly Sunday.  
</P>
<P>
	He had apparently lost control of his car and hit a tree and two  
utility poles. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said he may have been waiting for his father or warning  
other drivers of the downed electrical wires when another car hit 
the dangling lines. That caused a utility pole behind Herrera to 
snap. 
</P>
