<DOCNO> APW19990118.0155 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 17:45:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> White Sox, Simas in One-Year Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The Chicago White Sox have agreed to a $1.1  
million, one-year contract with right-hander Bill Simas, avoiding 
arbitration. 
</P>
<P>
	Simas, 27, made $250,000 last year, when he went 4-3 with 18  
saves and a 3.57 ERA in 60 games with the White Sox. 
</P>
<P>
	``I am very pleased we were able to reach an agreement with Bill  
that satisfied both sides,'' White Sox general manager Ron Schueler 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Simas limited opponents to a .206 batting average last season,  
the eighth-lowest in the American League. He is 10-13 with 21 saves 
and a 3.99 ERA during four seasons with the White Sox. 
</P>
</TEXT>
