<HEADLINE> Angels Pitcher To Have Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Anaheim Angels pitcher Jack McDowell will  
have exploratory arthroscopic surgery on his right shoulder Feb. 2. 
</P>
<P>
	McDowell, a right-hander who re-signed for $500,000 in December,  
was 5-3 record and a 5.09 ERA in 14 starts last season. He had two 
stints on the 15-day disabled list, once for an inflamed right 
elbow and another for a stress reaction in his right elbow. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1997, McDowell was hampered by right elbow problems while  
pitching for Cleveland and underwent arthroscopic surgery to 
alleviate pinching of soft tissue. During his comeback, he 
sustained an elbow bruise that sidelined him for the remainder of 
the season. 
</P>
<P>
	McDowell first signed with the Angels as a free agent last  
February. 
</P>
</TEXT>
