<HEADLINE> Gore To See Tornado Damage in Tenn. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Vice President Al Gore will fly home to  
Tennessee on Tuesday to console victims and assess damage from a 
tornado that killed six people and injured about 100 others in the 
Jackson area. 
</P>
<P>
	The vice president is expected to fly to Jackson early in the  
day, take a helicopter tour and then inspect destroyed homes. He 
also will stop at a hospital, his office said. 
</P>
<P>
	Gore has to be back in Washington by Tuesday night to sit behind  
the president at his State of the Union address in the House 
chamber. 
</P>
</TEXT>
