<DOCNO> APW19990118.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 14:57:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Details of $6B Housing Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Columbia National Mortgage Co. will make $6 billion in home  
mortgage loans available over five years to minorities and low- to 
moderate-income families under a housing discrimination settlement 
with the government to people in the District of Columbia and the 
following 26 states: 
</P>
<P>
	Connecticut, Delaware, Florida, Georgia, Idaho, Illinois,  
Indiana, Kentucky, Massachusetts, Maryland, Minnesota, North 
Carolina, North Dakota and New Hampshire. 
</P>
<P>
	Also New Jersey, New York, Ohio, Oklahoma, Pennsylvania, Rhode  
Island, South Carolina, Tennessee, Texas, Virginia, West Virginia 
and Wisconsin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
