<HEADLINE> Ohio St. Coach Held on Assault </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Ohio State offensive coordinator Mike  
Jacobs, charged with assaulting his former wife, was being held 
without bond today in the Franklin County Jail pending a court 
appearance Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Jacobs, 49, who turned himself in to authorities early today,  
faces misdemeanor charges of domestic violence and assault brought 
by his former wife, Robbin Jacobs. 
</P>
<P>
	Robbin Jacobs claimed in her police report that Jacobs struck  
her across the face several times as they were driving in his car 
on Interstate 270 about 12:15 a.m. Saturday. She also alleged he 
pulled her by the hair and pushed her against a car door. 
</P>
<P>
	Sheriff's deputies tried to arrest Jacobs at Ohio State's Woody  
Hayes Athletic Center Saturday morning, but were unable to find 
him. 
</P>
