<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-18 16:03:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Friends Gather for Ali's Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Muhammad Ali was invited into the ring by Mike  
Tyson at a birthday bash for The Greatest. 
</P>
<P>
	Actually, it was a cake shaped like a boxing ring that Tyson  
wheeled out at the private dinner party at the MGM Grand 
hotel-casino. Friends and family chanted Ali's name as he helped 
cut the cake. 
</P>
<P>
	Singer Gladys Knight, a longtime friend, was also on hand for  
Ali's 57th birthday Sunday. She and others watched a film that 
traced Ali's life from his birth in Louisville, Ky., as Cassius 
Clay Jr., to his 1960 Olympic gold medal and a career that was 
interrupted when he was stripped of his title for refusing to 
register for the draft. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was not only the greatest outside, he was the greatest  
inside,'' Knight said. 
</P>
<P>
	Longtime associate Gene Kilroy told of the time Ali gave a  
struggling senior citizens' home $300,000 during the height of his 
career. When he praised Ali for the good deed, Kilroy said the 
boxer told him: ``Kindness to others is the rent we pay for our 
time on Earth.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Kilroy also recalled a time when Ali learned a 5-year-old boy  
was dying of leukemia. He visited the boy before one of his fights 
and told the youngster, ``You're going to win your fight, and I'm 
going to win my fight.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ali visited the boy later when he took a turn for the worse, and  
the boy told him: ``I'm going to meet God and I'm going to tell him 
I know you.'' The boy died three weeks later, Kilroy said. 
</P>
<P>
	Neither Tyson nor Ali spoke to the crowd, although both posed  
for pictures. 
</P>
<P>
	Tyson attended the party 24 hours after defeating Francois Botha  
at the casino. Tyson hadn't fought since he was stripped of his 
boxing license 19 months ago for biting Evander Holyfield's ears. 
</P>
<P>
	Ali, who has Parkinson's syndrome, watched Tyson's comeback  
fight and had shown his support for him as he tried to get his 
license back. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
