<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brave Act Wins at Santa Anita </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Brave Act won his fourth straight race  
Monday, capturing the $150,000 San Marcos Handicap by 1 3/4 lengths 
over Ferrari at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Goncalino Almeida, Brave Act covered 1 1/4 miles on the  
turf in 2:04 1-5 and paid $6.60, $3.40 and $3.20. Ferrari returned 
$7.20 and $5.20, while Native Desert was another half-length back 
in third and paid $5.20 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	``I had my horse in a good spot the while way,'' Almeida said.  
``I just waited until the turn for home, and when I asked him, he 
made his good run as usual. This horse just has so much ability and 
is willing to do anything.'' 
</P>
<P>
	British-bred Brave Act hasn't finished worse than second in his  
last eight starts dating to September 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory, worth $90,000, increased Brave Act's career  
earnings to $597,807, with nine wins in 17 starts for owner Sidney 
H. Craig, the husband of diet maven Jenny Craig. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
