<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Theimer Moves to Sacramento Bureau </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Sharon Theimer, correspondent for The  
Associated Press in Madison, Wis., has been promoted to 
correspondent in charge of the AP's bureau in Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Monday by San Francisco Chief of  
Bureau Dan Day. 
</P>
<P>
	Theimer, 28, joined the AP in Milwaukee in 1992 and worked in  
the Detroit bureau in early 1993 before returning to Milwaukee. She 
was appointed correspondent in Madison in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	Theimer, a native of Appleton, Wis., grew up in Kaukauna, Wis.,  
and is a graduate of Marquette University in Milwaukee. 
</P>
<P>
	Before joining the AP, she worked at The Post-Crescent in  
Appleton, The Hartford (Conn.) Courant and The Milwaukee Journal. 
</P>
<P>
	Theimer succeeds Rich Harris, who became news editor in  
Hartford. 
</P>
</TEXT>
