<HEADLINE> Islanders Acquire Center Janney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	UNIONDALE, N.Y. (AP) -- The New York Islanders have acquired  
center Craig Janney from the Tampa Bay Lightning for a sixth-round 
draft pick in 1999. 
</P>
<P>
	Announcement of the deal was made Monday by Islanders general  
manager-coach Mike Milbury. 
</P>
<P>
	``Throughout his career, Craig has consistently proven that he  
can distribute the puck and produce offensively,'' Milbury said in 
a statement. ``Since that is obviously an area were we are lacking, 
I'm certain he can help us.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In 742 career games with Boston, St. Louis, San Jose, Winnipeg,  
Phoenix and Tampa Bay, Janney has 187 goals and 559 assists for 746 
points. Janney, 31, had four goals and 18 assists in 38 games for 
the Lightning this season. 
</P>
